set.incubator.apache.org/\">Apache Superset (incubating)</a> - Apache Superset (incubating) is a modern, enterprise-ready business intelligence web application</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T02:19:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://kudu.apache.org/\">Apache Kudu</a> - Kudu provides a combination of fast inserts/updates and efficient columnar scans to enable multiple real-time analytic workloads across a single storage layer, complementing HDFS and Apache HBase.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T02:13:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Machine learning and Big Data analytics</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://bigdl-project.github.io/\">BigDL</a> - BigDL is a distributed deep learning library for Apache Spark; with BigDL, users can write their deep learning applications as standard Spark programs, which can directly run on top of existing Spark or Hadoop clusters.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T02:12:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Search</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://lucene.apache.org/solr/\">Apache Solr</a> - Apache Solr is an open source search platform built upon a Java library called Lucene.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T02:07:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Distributed Computing and Programming</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://livy.incubator.apache.org/\">Apache Livy (incubating)</a> - Apache Livy (incubating) is web service that exposes a REST interface for managing long running Apache Spark contexts in your cluster. With Livy, new applications can be built on top of Apache Spark that require fine grained interaction with many Spark contexts.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T02:06:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hadoop and Big Data Events</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://databricks.com/sparkaisummit\">Spark Summit</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T02:02:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pypi.python.org/pypi/snakebite/\">snakebite</a> - A pure python HDFS client</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T01:58:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Realtime Data Processing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://pulsar.incubator.apache.org/\">Apache Pulsar (incubating)</a> - Apache Pulsar (incubating) is a highly scalable, low latency messaging platform running on commodity hardware. It provides simple pub-sub semantics over topics, guaranteed at-least-once delivery of messages, automatic cursor management for subscribers, and cross-datacenter replication.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T01:55:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hadoop and Big Data Events</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dataworkssummit.com/\">DataWorks Summit</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T01:50:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://parquet.apache.org/\">Apache Parquet</a> - Apache Parquet is a columnar storage format available to any project in the Hadoop ecosystem, regardless of the choice of data processing framework, data model or programming language.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T01:46:40.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"youngwookim/awesome-hadoop","categoryHTML":"<h2>SQL on Hadoop</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://impala.apache.org/\">Apache Impala</a> - Apache Impala is an open source massively parallel processing (MPP) SQL query engine for data stored in a computer cluster running Apache Hadoop. Impala has been described as the open-source equivalent of Google F1, which inspired its development in 2012.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-11T01:33:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"donnemartin